Python Firewall with GUI
This project is a basic Python-based firewall built using Scapy and Tkinter. It allows real-time packet monitoring, customizable rule-based filtering, and a user-friendly GUI.
ðŸ“¦ Features
    Live Packet Monitoring (via scapy.sniff)
    Rule-based Filtering (IP, ports, protocols)
    Graphical User Interface (Tkinter-based)
    Logging & Alerts
    Safe Shutdown & Error Handling
requirements
    Python 3.7+
    Modules:
        scapy
        tkinter (comes with Python)
        threading
bash code:pip install scapy

day 8 contains the firewall.py python code the GUI will launch and display live packets. You can apply filtering rules from the rule file or via input fields.

| Test                  | Tool Used | Rule Used          | Expected Output | Observed |
| --------------------- | --------- | ------------------ | --------------- | -------- |
| Ping 127.0.0.1        | `ping`    | No ICMP rules      | Default allow   | âœ…        |
| Curl to 10.0.2.15:443 | `curl`    | Block rule         | Packet blocked  | âœ…        |
| Curl to google.com:80 | `curl`    | Allow port 80      | Packet allowed  | âœ…        |
| nmap to 10.0.2.15     | `nmap`    | Block IP 10.0.2.15 | TCP/443 blocked | âœ…        |


